Here's the `ispersonal` function that meets your requirements:

```julia
abstract type AbstractVehicle end

struct Car <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Motorcycle <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Bus <: AbstractVehicle end
struct Truck <: AbstractVehicle end

function ispersonal(vehicle::AbstractVehicle)
    if vehicle == Car() || vehicle == Motorcycle()
        return true
    else
        return false
    end
end

@assert ispersonal(Car()) == true
@assert ispersonal(Motorcycle()) == true
@assert ispersonal(Bus()) == false
@assert ispersonal(Truck()) == false
@assert ispersonal(AbstractVehicle()) == false
```

This function checks if the provided vehicle is of type `Car` or `Motorcycle`, and returns `true` if so, indicating that it is a personal vehicle. It returns `false` for all other types of `AbstractVehicle`, including `Bus`, `Truck`, and any other custom subtypes.
